        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 2 at 5:56PM EDT until July 2 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>SVRDTX

The National Weather Service in Detroit/Pontiac has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Genesee County in southeastern Michigan...

* Until 700 PM EDT.

* At 556 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Crossroads
Village, or near Flint, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Flint and Burton around 600 PM EDT.
Davison around 605 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Genesee.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
